author: Jasbir s

text:
Hi Akshat, 

I highly appreciate the intent with which you started this channel - to increase financial literacy, while you make this channel a stream of passive income yourself. There's nothing wrong with that. 

However, it's disappointing to see how you've increasingly pivoted to 'clickbait thumbnails' that set unrealistic expectations among young inexperienced investors, that is your audience. Ex. 20,000 in 1 month, 2x returns in 15 days.

You might say that you discuss everything in detail during the full video and encourage responsible financial behaviour. But, you shouldn't resort to the clickbait method to get views, similar to the strategy for any random Youtube video. Money management is also serious. 

These THUMBNAILS need to go, sorry!
